Description: Fragment of neck and oval handle to sharpish turn of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine red-buff; cream slip. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Name Nikagis. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0392.30?
Bibliographic references: Stoddart 1847 / Memoir on the inscribed pottery of Rhodes, Cnidus and other Greek Cities (193)
